<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3746] updateLog should fail to init if there is no _version_ field in schema.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3746</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per irc conversation with yonik, it&apos;s not clear if updateLog works correctly in all situations if there is no &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#95;version&amp;#95;&lt;/tt&gt; field in the schema...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it&apos;s certainly not tested&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3432&quot; title=&quot;deleteByQuery silently ignored if updateLog is enabled, but {{_version_}} field does not exist in schema &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-3432&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-3432&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; makes it clear there are at least some problematic sitautions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;For these reasons, updateLog initialization should fail fast with a clear error if there is no &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#95;version&amp;#95;&lt;/tt&gt; field in the schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(we can always relax this restriction later if people write the code/tests for it)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
